                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " 0.5 OR 1 CM THICK NATURAL LITHIUM TARGETS. THE",
                " PROTON BEAM WAS BENT BY A MAGNET AND STOPPED IN A",
                " WELL-SHIELDED GRAPHITE BLOCK. THE NEUTRON BEAM WAS",
                " SHAPED BY A SYSTEM OF THREE IRON OR BRASS COLLIMATORS.",
                " THE FIRST WAS 1.6 M LONG WITH AN INITIAL DIAMETER OF",
                " 10 MM, THE SECOND WAS 60 CM LONG AND STARTED 4.7 M",
                " FROM THE LI TARGET, AND HAD A FINAL DIAMETER OF 17.1",
                " MM, THE THIRD WAS 80 CM LONG AND SERVED AS A HALO",
                " COLLIMATOR. AT THE EXPERIMENTAL POSITION, 6.7 M FROM",
                " THE LI TARGET, THE BEAM DIAMETER WAS 20 MM."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".A LIQUID HYDROGEN TARGET, LIMITED BY TWO 35 MM DIA-",
                " METER BY 6 MICROMETER THICK ALUMINIZED MYLAR WINDOWS."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " THE DEUTERONS, PRODUCED IN A NARROW FORWARD"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " CONE, WERE DETECTED AND IDENTIFIED USING A",
                " PLASTIC SCINTILLATOR TELESCOPE AND TIME-OF-FLIGHT",
                " TECHNIQUES."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " CHARGED PARTICLES WERE DETECTED BY TWO NE102",
                " PLASTIC SCINTILLATORS. THE FIRST, 0.2 MM THICK AND 16",
                " CM IN DIAMETER, WITH A 3 CM HOLE IN ITS CENTER FOR",
                " PASSAGE OF THE NEUTRON BEAM, WAS LOCATED AT 50 CM FROM",
                " THE HYDROGEN TARGET. THE SECOND, 1.5 CM THICK AND",
                " 68 X 64 CM2 IN AREA, WITH A 5 CM HOLE, WAS LOCATED AT",
                " 1.57 M FROM THE FIRST DETECTOR. A 0.1 MM THICK PLASTIC",
                " SCINTILLATOR, PLACED BEFORE THE HYDROGEN TARGET,",
                " VETOED CHARGED PARTICLES CONTAMINATING THE BEAM. IN",
                " ADDITION, A 12 X 3 CM2 AND 4 MM THICK PLASTIC SCIN-",
                " TILLATOR WAS USED TO DETECT PROTONS SCATTERED AT 7",
                " DEGREES LAB ANGLE. THE LATTER INFORMATION WAS USED",
                " FOR CROSS SECTION NORMALIZATION."
              ]
            }
